FBIS4-43605 "drweu118_p_94009" FBIS-WEU-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 GREECE Heart Surgeon Says Papandreou `Doing Very Well' Heart Surgeon Says Papandreou `Doing Very Well' NC1806153794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1500 GMT 18 Jun 94 NC1806153794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Excerpt] The famous cardiac surgeon Magdi Yacoub, who is participating in an international cardiological conference at Iraklion, Crete, has expressed his satisfaction with the health of Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou. During a news conference, Yacoub told correspondents that the Greek prime minister is doing very well. [passage omitted]
